Class JavaProcessManagerFactory<T extends Runnable & Serializable>

  • Object
    • JavaProcessManagerFactory<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - A type variable implementing the Runnable and Serializable interfaces that defines the base class of the startup tasks of the created JavaProcessManager instances.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    ProcessManagerFactory
    public class JavaProcessManagerFactory<T extends Runnable & Serializable>
extends Object
implements ProcessManagerFactory
    An implementation of the ProcessManagerFactory interface for the creation of JavaProcessManager instances using a single ProcessBuilder instance.

    • Constructor Detail

      • JavaProcessManagerFactory

        public JavaProcessManagerFactory​(JavaProcessConfig config,
                                 T initTask,
                                 T wrapUpTask,
                                 Long keepAliveTime)
        Constructs an instance based on the specified JVM config, keepAliveTime, initialization task, and wrap-up task which are used for the for the management of all Java processes of the pool.
        Parameters:
        config - The JVM config for starting the Java process.
        initTask - The task to execute in each process on startup, before the process starts accepting submissions. If it is null, no taks are executed on startup.
        wrapUpTask - The task to execute in each process before it is terminated. If it is null, no wrap-up task is executed.
        keepAliveTime - The number of milliseconds after which idle processes are terminated.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - If the config is null or contains invalid values.
